We have implementated the extra credit. We used the PA3 implementation in our code. 
This is a client server implementation of PA3. The client will ask the server to
process city name requests. The server will contain the database of 3 most used
words in a city. The client will ask the server for these, will recieve them 
and create a clientX.in.result file

Steps to run:
make

On server terminal:
./twitterTrend_server port_number num_threads
EXAMPLE: ./twitterTrend_server 4036

On client terminal:
./twitterTrend_client server_host_name server_port_number file_path
EXAMPLE: ./twitterTrend_client lind40-20.cselabs.umn.edu 4036 ../client1.in

OR FOR MULTIPLE CLIENTS
//You can use multiple client.in files on a server request

./twitterTrend_client server_host_name server_port_number file_path1 file_path2 file_path3 .....
EXAMPLE: ./twitterTrend_client lind40-20.cselabs.umn.edu 4036 ../client1.in ../client2.in
